  "slug": "whose-success-do-i-struggle-to-celebrate-why",
  "title": "Whose Success Do I Struggle to Celebrate? Why?",
  "subtitle": "A journal prompt set for examining comparison and the triggered response to other women's financial wins",
  "excerpt": "A journal set for examining the comparison response directly, who specifically triggers it, what story runs underneath it, and what the trigger is actually pointing at in your own money situation.",
  "type": "PRACTICE",
  "sourceNotes": "Written for homemade.education.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A journal set for examining the comparison trigger. The purpose is not to decide you should feel differently. It's to find out what the triggered feeling is actually about in your own money story.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "New to journal practice? Read ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "journal prompts as practice",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "/mindset/journal-prompts-as-practice"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " first.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The practice",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Warm-up",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Think of a recent time when another woman's success made me feel something other than glad for her. What happened?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Describe it plainly. What did she do or announce? What did you feel?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Is there a category of success that triggers me more than others?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Money in particular? A specific kind of business or income? A lifestyle that looks a certain way?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Closer in",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What does her win make me believe about my own chances?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Write the logic even if you know it isn't rational. The belief doesn't have to make sense to be running.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What is the comparison actually pointing at in my own situation?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Is there something in your own money situation that feels stalled, stuck, or behind where you expected to be? That's usually what the comparison is about.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What is one concrete thing I could do to move in the direction her win is making me want to go?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The trigger can be redirected. Name the action it's pointing toward, even if you're not ready to take it.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
